text.section:
"Cost" includes:
The purchase price of property;
The cost to acquire any right, title, or interest in property;
The cost of any improvements made to property;
The amount to be paid to discharge each obligation necessary or desirable to vest title to any part of property in an authority or other owner;
The cost of any property, right, easement, franchise, and permit associated with a project;
The cost of labor, machinery, and equipment necessary to implement a project;
Financing charges;
Interest and reserves for principal and interest and for improvements;
The cost of revenue and cost estimates, engineering and legal services, plans, specifications, studies, surveys, and other expenses necessary or incident to determining the feasibility or practicability of a project;
Administrative expenses; and
Other expenses as necessary or incident to:
Financing a project;
Acquiring and improving a project;
Placing a project in operation, including reasonable provisions for working capital; and
Operating and maintaining a project.

section.section:
"Project" includes:
Acquiring land or an interest in land;
Acquiring structures, equipment, and furnishings located on a property;
Acquiring property that is functionally related and subordinate to a project; and
Obtaining or contracting for any services necessary for the rehabilitation of a property.
